
Java Programming Lab Questions
1. Write a Java program to print the sum (addition), multiply, subtract, divide, and remainder of two numbers.**
2. Write a Java program to print the area and perimeter of a circle and rectangle.**
3. Write a Java program to swap two variables with or without a third variable.**
4. Write a Java program to compare two numbers.**
5. Write a Java program to accept a number and check whether the number is even or not. Prints 1 if the number is even or 0 if odd.**
6. Write a Java program that accepts three integers from the user and returns true if two or more of them (integers) have the same rightmost digit. The integers are non-negative.**
7. Any year is entered through the keyboard, write a program to determine whether the year is leap or not. Use the logical operators `&&` and `||`.
8. Write a simple Java program to calculate a factorial of a number.**
9. Write a program that takes the x-y coordinates of a point in the Cartesian plane and prints a message telling either an axis on which the point lies or the quadrant in which it is found.**

These are the tasks specified in your Java Programming Lab.